  "theorem": {
    "latex_statement": "\\begin{theorem}[Global $T/K\\cong V_4$ freeness, finite certificate form]\\label{thm:global-tk-freeness}\nIn the certified Endpoint-24 affine-defect atlas extension atlas, the quotient $T/K$ has order four and is isomorphic to $V_4$.  The L7 certificate verifies that it preserves every endpoint and acts freely on all $7040$ square-mask pairs.  Consequently each endpoint stratum, and each certified endpoint-24 class stratum, has record count equal to four times its $T/K$ quotient-orbit count.\n\\end{theorem}",
    "name": "Global T/K=V4 freeness theorem, finite certificate form",
    "statement": "In the certified Endpoint-24 affine-defect atlas extension atlas, the L7 quotient T/K is V4 of order four, preserves every endpoint, and acts freely on the 7040 square-mask pairs.  Hence every endpoint and every endpoint-24 class has record count equal to four times its T/K quotient-orbit count.",
